article.headline: Pacific 80, California Maritime 42
article.story: STOCKTON, Calif. -- Lorenzo McCloud scored 14 points, Sama Taku chipped in with 13 and Pacific dominated inside play in an 80-42 rout over Cal Maritime on Friday night. Pacific (6-6) outscored the Keelhaulers 48-14 inside the paint and shot 58.2 percent from the field in the game, making 32 of 55 attempts. The Tigers out-rebounded Cal Maritime 46-25, held them to just 27.9 percent shooting and didn't put the Keelhaulers on the free-throw line all night. Three other players were in double figures scoring for Pacific with Tim Thomas, Tony Gill and Travis Fulton each scoring 11 points for the Tigers, which led by 19 at halftime and outscored the Keelhaulers 38-19 in the second half. Keven Campbell scored 13 points to lead Cal Maritime (10-4), an NAIA program, and Howie Manzo pitched in with 10 points for a team which made only seven baskets the entire second half.
